==English==

===Etymology===
:old French ''escalate'', meaning ''scarlet cloth''.  If you go further you will discover that scarlet comes from {{Pers.}} saqirlat "a kind of rich cloth," variant of siqillat "scarlet cloth, rich cloth," of unknown origin (Arabic siqillat "fine cloth" probably is ult. from [[Persian]]).

